ROMAN COMEDY

6. In various parts of Italy there early grew up several kinds of mummery and buffoonery similar to the Greek popu- lar impersonations out of which comedy originated. The Romans therefore had native materials out of which they might have developed a drama of their own3 but before they had done so they came under the spell of Greek lit- erature.
